# The Core AI dead end (2026-07-15). A 4 GB float32 Stable Diffusion 1.5 export that works,
# kept on disk because it cost real time to make — but it is an artifact, not a foundation,
# and the direction was called off. See `coreai-export/README.md` and HISTORY 2026-07-15.
#
# Ignored rather than committed: 4 GB in git history follows every clone forever, and this
# is a model we decided not to use. The folder's README is ignored along with it — HISTORY.md
# is the durable record, not that file.
coreai-export/

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PRIVATE, BUT VERSIONED — tracked in the local-only .thomas-docs-git, NEVER pushed.
# See STUDIO_REPO_HYGIENE.md. Public GitHub holds code + the docs/ website only; every-
# thing below is committed to .thomas-docs-git (full history + rollback) and ignored here
# so a stray `git add -A` can never push it. Drive that git with tools/docs.sh. This is
# the two-gits-one-folder mechanism — the real answer to "committed locally, only code
# public," which a single git can't do.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.thomas-docs-git/

